  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "The hyphen is a small mark with a precise job: it glues words into one idea. A well-known fact, a fast-paced day, hand-eye coordination - the hyphen tells the reader these words travel together. Miss it and the meaning loosens; copy editors earn their keep catching exactly this."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The hyphen lives on the top row, just left of the equals key - a reach up and to the right for your right pinky, no Shift. Stretch the pinky up, tap, and bring the hand back to the home row. Let only that one finger travel; the others stay anchored."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "✍️",
      "title": "No spaces around it",
      "text": "A hyphen sits tight against the words it joins: well-known, not well - known. Spaces would break the very link you are trying to make. Glue means glue - no air on either side."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "-",
      "baseReps": 15,
      "keys": ["-"],
      "target": "- - - - - - - - - - - - - - -",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The hyphen",
      "hint": "Right pinky reaches up to the key left of equals, then home. No Shift."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "well-known fast-paced hand-eye so-so well-formed",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Joining words",
      "hint": "Tap the hyphen tight between the words - no spaces around it."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Now the marks earn their place in full sentences. Read each line, then type it through - hyphens snug inside the compounds, a single space between separate words."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "A hyphen is the difference between a small business man and a small-business man. Place it on purpose.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "well-known truth: write well-formed sentences. fast-paced work needs hand-eye care. so-so days happen.",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Compounds in sentences",
      "hint": "No spaces inside a hyphenated pair; normal spacing everywhere else."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Steps done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
